# DevMemory Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and configure your settings

# ==== AWS BEDROCK CONFIGURATION ====
# Required for AI-powered features (embeddings, summaries)
# Get these from your AWS Console
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-aws-access-key
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-aws-secret-key

# ==== MICROSOFT 365 INTEGRATION ====
# Optional - Leave blank to disable M365 integration
# To enable: Register an Azure AD application and get these values
AZURE_CLIENT_ID=
AZURE_AUTHORITY=https://login.microsoftonline.com/common

# ==== APPLICATION SETTINGS ====
NODE_ENV=production

# ==== INSTALLATION NOTES ====
# 1. Copy this file to .env (without .example)
# 2. Configure AWS credentials for AI features
# 3. Optionally configure Azure for M365 integration  
# 4. The app will work without M365 integration
# 5. ChromaDB will use fallback embeddings if AWS Bedrock unavailable

# ==== FRESH MACHINE SETUP ====
# Required software:
# - Node.js 18+
# - npm 8+
# - Git
# 
# Installation:
# npm install
# npm run build
# npm start